<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Erofs on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/erofs/</link><description>Recent content in Erofs on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/erofs/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] C errno 30 EROFS — Read-only file system</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-30/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-30/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-30-erofs--read-only-file-system"&gt;[Solution] C errno 30 EROFS — Read-only file system&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Read-only file system occurs when a system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to 30. This error indicates that the requested operation cannot be performed due to the specific condition described by EROFS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trying to write to a file system mounted as read-only.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Attempting to create or modify files on a read-only media.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modifying system directories that are intentionally read-only.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Trying to remount a file system without proper permissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;fcntl.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;errno.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;string.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/proc/sysrq-trigger&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_WRONLY);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;fprintf&lt;/span&gt;(stderr, &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;open failed: %s (errno %d)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;strerror&lt;/span&gt;(errno), errno);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;close&lt;/span&gt;(fd);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;sys/vfs.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;stdio.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;#include&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;&amp;lt;errno.h&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;main&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;void&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;struct&lt;/span&gt; statfs buf;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (&lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;statfs&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt;buf) &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (buf.f_flags &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;&amp;amp;&lt;/span&gt; ST_RDONLY) {
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;printf&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Root file system is read-only&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;\n&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; }
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;}
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-13/"&gt;errno-13 EACCES&lt;/a&gt; — permission denied.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-30/"&gt;errno-30 EROFS&lt;/a&gt; — read-only file system (self).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-28/"&gt;errno-28 ENOSPC&lt;/a&gt; — no space left on device.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C errno EROFS — Read-only file system Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-erofs/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/errno-erofs/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="solution-c-errno-erofs--read-only-file-system-fix"&gt;[Solution] C errno EROFS — Read-only file system Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When a process attempts to modify a file on a read-only filesystem, the system call fails and sets &lt;code&gt;errno&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;EROFS&lt;/code&gt;. This error occurs when the filesystem is mounted read-only, either by configuration or due to filesystem corruption triggering a read-only remount.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The filesystem is mounted with the &lt;code&gt;ro&lt;/code&gt; (read-only) option.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The filesystem was remounted read-only after I/O errors (kernel protective measure).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The root filesystem is read-only during early boot or in embedded systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CD-ROM, DVD, or write-protected media is mounted.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remount the filesystem read-write if modification is needed, or avoid writing to read-only filesystems.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] C Read-only file system: EROFS</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/read-only-file-system/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/read-only-file-system/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="read-only-file-system-erofs"&gt;Read-only file system: EROFS&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;EROFS occurs when you try to write to a filesystem mounted as read-only. This can happen on CD-ROMs, certain mount options, or when the filesystem has errors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 1: Writing to read-only mount
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/mnt/cdrom/file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_WRONLY); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EROFS
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 2: Filesystem remounted read-only due to errors
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Linux remounts ext4 as read-only on corruption
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Cause 3: Writing to /boot or similar protected path
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/boot/kernel&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_WRONLY); &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// EROFS
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-remount-as-read-write"&gt;Fix 1: Remount as read-write&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mount -o remount,rw /mnt/data
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-check-filesystem-errors"&gt;Fix 2: Check filesystem errors&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;fsck /dev/sda1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-writable-path"&gt;Fix 3: Use writable path&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-c" data-lang="c"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;// Write to /tmp instead
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; fd &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#a6e22e"&gt;open&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;/tmp/file.txt&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;, O_WRONLY &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;|&lt;/span&gt; O_CREAT, &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0644&lt;/span&gt;);
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/permission-denied-file/"&gt;Permission denied&lt;/a&gt; — EACCES.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/no-space-left/"&gt;No space left&lt;/a&gt; — ENOSPC.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/c/input-output-error/"&gt;Input/output error&lt;/a&gt; — EIO.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Linux Read-Only File System — Remount Read-Write Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/readonly-filesystem/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/os/linux/readonly-filesystem/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="linux-read-only-file-system"&gt;Linux: Read-Only File System&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The &lt;code&gt;Read-only file system&lt;/code&gt; error (EROFS) means the system tried to write to a filesystem that is mounted as read-only. This can happen because the filesystem was explicitly mounted read-only, the kernel detected corruption and remounted it read-only for safety, or a hardware issue prevented writes. Until the underlying cause is fixed, all write operations to that filesystem will fail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Filesystem has errors and was remounted read-only by the kernel&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explicit mount option &lt;code&gt;ro&lt;/code&gt; was used&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disk hardware failure triggering read-only fallback&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NFS or network filesystem server unreachable&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;code&gt;/etc/fstab&lt;/code&gt; misconfiguration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Filesystem corruption from power loss&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-check-which-filesystems-are-read-only"&gt;1. Check Which Filesystems Are Read-Only&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Check mount status&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mount | grep &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;ro,&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or check specific mount points&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;mount | grep &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34; / &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Example output:&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>